  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the lives of People with Albinism</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Albino children between the ages of 3 to 16 years in the districts of Jinja, Mayuge and Namutumba in Uganda have challenges regarding their lives i.e. their health, low levels of education and stigmatization. UPIMAC, through 3 key interventions namely; health, education and advocacy interventions is advocating to help these helpless children through fighting skin cancer, ensuring Albinos go back to school and advocating the Ugandan government to include Albino children in their programs yearly.</narrative>
  </description>
